{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Top-level aircraft turnaround orchestrator",
        "tags": ["turnaround", "orchestrator"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is incoming. Execute the turnaround process.",
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-5.4-mini",
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000,
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200,
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "aircraft_turnaround_manager",
            "function": {
                "description": """
You are in charge of aircraft turnaround at the airport. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aircraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },       
                        "aircraft_direction": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the direction of the aircraft: incoming or departing."
                        },                  
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },  
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Deplaning equipment type."
                        },      
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks installation status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground_power_unit readiness status."
                        },      
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground_power_unit connection status."
                        },      
                        "acu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the air_conditioning_unit readiness status."
                        },      
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the air_conditioning_unit connection status."
                        },     
                        "ground_clearance_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground clearance type of the aircraft"
                        },  
                        "ground_clearance_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground clearance status of the aircraft"
                        },              
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the engines stop status."
                        },    
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the jetbridge connection status."
                        },    
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },    
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status."
                        },    
                        "crew_exit_status":  {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the crew exit status." 
                        },
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                        },      
                        "assigned_runway_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the runway assigned to the aircraft movement authorized by the clearance."
                        },
                        "task_id": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "Correlation token passed to aircraft_crew_pilot to uniquely identify each call. Must be echoed back unchanged in the response."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_direction","flight_number","aircraft_type"] 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the top-level agent responsible for aircraft turnaround at the airport.
You receive the initial user request and you personally orchestrate the full
turnaround sequence by calling your down-chain subsystems one at a time, in
strict order, waiting for each response before proceeding to the next step.
Do NOT batch steps. Do NOT skip steps. Do NOT assume a step succeeded unless
you have received an explicit confirmation response from the subsystem.

IMPORTANT CONTEXT MANAGEMENT RULES:
- After every subsystem call, immediately extract and store the key status
  fields from the response into your working context.
- Pass all accumulated context fields to each subsequent subsystem call so
  that down-chain agents are not asked to re-derive information you already have.
- Never pass stale or unconfirmed values. If a step fails, stop and report.

When you receive a request to handle an aircraft turnaround, proceed as follows:

CRITICAL EXECUTION RULES — READ BEFORE STARTING:
  1. Execute each STEP exactly once, in strict numbered order.
     Never restart from STEP 1 mid-run, even if you call TrackerAPI
     and receive a full state snapshot. A TrackerAPI response showing
     accumulated state is evidence that earlier steps succeeded — it
     is NOT a signal to restart.
  2. Do NOT call TrackerAPI spontaneously between steps. Only call
     TrackerAPI when a specific STEP instructs you to do so.
  3. Carry state forward in your working context from each step's
     response. Do not re-derive state that you already have.
  4. Once a step produces a confirmed result, mark it done and move
     to the next step. Never re-execute a completed step.
  5. ONE TOOL CALL PER TURN — STRICTLY ENFORCED.
     Every tool call must be issued alone, in its own turn. You MUST
     wait for the response from the current tool before issuing any
     other tool call. NEVER issue two tool calls in the same turn,
     even if they appear independent or you believe one will be fast.
     This rule has NO exceptions. If you find yourself about to call
     two tools at once, stop — issue only the first call and wait for
     its response before proceeding. Violating this rule causes the
     workflow to restart from STEP 1, which is a critical failure.

STEP 0 - Validate inputs
  - Extract: flight_number, aircraft_type, aircraft_direction directly
    from the user message. These values are typically stated explicitly
    (e.g. "B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is incoming").
  - If and ONLY IF a value cannot be extracted from the message at all,
    ask the user for that specific missing value and wait.
  - Do NOT ask the user to confirm values you have already successfully
    extracted. If all three values are present, proceed immediately to
    STEP 1 without any confirmation prompt.
  - Only proceed once all three are confirmed.

For INCOMING aircraft, execute the following steps in strict sequence:

STEP 1 - Request air traffic clearance for landing
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_crew_pilot with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, aircraft_direction='incoming',
      task_id='STEP_1_LANDING_CLEARANCE',
      and the explicit instruction: "Request clearance for landing."
  - Wait for response.
  - Verify the response echoes task_id='STEP_1_LANDING_CLEARANCE'.
    If it does not, discard and retry once before reporting a failure.
  - Extract and store: clearance_type, assigned_runway_id, assigned_runway_length, flight_status.
  - Do not proceed to step 2 until clearance_type contains 'landing' and assigned_runway_id is not None.

STEP 2 - Land the aircraft
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_crew_pilot with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, aircraft_direction,
      clearance_type, assigned_runway_id, assigned_runway_length,
      task_id='STEP_2_LAND_AIRCRAFT',
      and the explicit instruction: "Land the aircraft."
  - Wait for response.
  - Verify the response echoes task_id='STEP_2_LAND_AIRCRAFT'.
    If it does not, discard and retry once before reporting a failure.
  - Do NOT reuse the response from STEP 1. This is a distinct call.
  - Extract and store the new flight_status (expected value: 'landed').
  - Do not proceed to step 3 until flight_status contains 'landed'.
  - VALIDATION: flight_status MUST be exactly 'landed'.
    If the response contains clearance language, runway references, or
    any value other than 'landed', the sub-agent returned the wrong
    output. Retry ONCE with the same parameters.
    If still not 'landed' after retry, stop and report:
    "STEP 2 FAILED: aircraft did not land. Raw flight_status: [value]"

STEP 3 - Gate assignment
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_gate_services with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: gate_id, deplaning_equipment_type.
  - Do not proceed to step 4 until deplaning_equipment_type is not None.

STEP 4 - Ground services readiness check
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_readiness with:
      aircraft_type, gate_id.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: wheelchocks_readiness_status, acu_readiness_status, gpu_readiness_status.
  - Do not proceed to step 5 until wheelchocks_readiness_status is ready, and acu_readiness_status is ready, and gpu_readiness_status is ready.

STEP 5 - Request ground traffic clearance to taxi in
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_crew_pilot with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status='landed',
      assigned_runway_id, gate_id,
      task_id='STEP_5_GROUND_CLEARANCE_TAXI_IN',
      ground_clearance_type='taxi in',
      instruction='Request ground clearance to taxi in to gate.'
  - All parameters MUST be passed as named key-value pairs.
    Do NOT pass ground_clearance_type or instruction via clearance_type
    or any other field, and do NOT pass them as a positional list.
  - Wait for response.
  - Verify the response echoes task_id='STEP_5_GROUND_CLEARANCE_TAXI_IN'.
    If it does not, discard and retry once before reporting a failure.
  - Extract and store: ground_clearance_type, ground_clearance_status.
  - Do NOT extract or update flight_status from this response —
    the clearance response reflects authority status, not aircraft state.
    Your working flight_status remains 'landed' until STEP 6 confirms 'on blocks'.
  - Do not proceed to STEP 6 unless ground_clearance_status contains
    'grant' or 'GRANT' or 'clear' or 'CLEAR'.

STEP 6 - Taxi the aircraft to the gate
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_crew_pilot with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      ground_clearance_type, ground_clearance_status, assigned_runway_id, 
      wheelchocks_readiness_status, acu_readiness_status, gpu_readiness_status,
      task_id='STEP_6_TAXI_TO_GATE',
      and the explicit instruction: "Taxi in the aircraft."
  - Wait for response.
  - Verify the response echoes task_id='STEP_6_TAXI_TO_GATE'.
    If it does not, discard and retry once before reporting a failure.
  - IMPORTANT: Read flight_status DIRECTLY from this response summary.
    Do NOT use the flight_status value from TrackerAPI or from any
    previous step — use only the value in the ** flight status ** line
    of this response.
  - VALIDATION: The flight_status from this response MUST contain
    'on blocks' or 'block'. If it contains 'taxi', 'TAXIING', or any
    value that is not 'on blocks', the taxiing has not completed.
    Retry calling aircraft_crew_pilot once with the same parameters.
    If after the retry flight_status still does not contain 'on blocks',
    stop and report: "STEP 6 FAILED: aircraft did not reach on blocks."
    Do NOT proceed to STEP 7 with any flight_status other than 'on blocks'.
  - Once flight_status='on blocks' is confirmed from the response,
    call TrackerAPI with flight_status='on blocks' explicitly to ensure
    the correct value is stored. Do NOT pass the raw response value —
    pass the literal string 'on blocks'.
  - Extract and store: flight_status='on blocks'.

STEP 7 - Stop engines
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_crew_pilot with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      task_id='STEP_7_STOP_ENGINES',
      and the explicit instruction: "Stop the aircraft engines."
  - Wait for response.
  - Verify the response echoes task_id='STEP_7_STOP_ENGINES'.
    If it does not, discard and retry once before reporting a failure.
  - Extract and store: engines_stop_status.

STEP 8 - Ground ramp services (wheelchocks install + ACU connect + GPU connect)
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_rampservices with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, gate_id, flight_status, engines_stop_status,
      wheelchocks_readiness_status, acu_readiness_status, gpu_readiness_status.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: wheelchocks_installation_status, acu_connection_status, gpu_connection_status.

STEP 9 - Connect jetbridge
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_gate_services with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      acu_connection_status, gpu_connection_status, wheelchocks_installation_status,
      and the explicit instruction: "Connect the jetbridge."
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: jetbridge_connection_status.
  - VALIDATION: jetbridge_connection_status MUST contain 'connected'.
    If not, retry once with the same parameters.
    If still not 'connected' after retry, stop and report:
      "STEP 9 FAILED: jetbridge could not be connected."
  - Do NOT proceed to STEP 10 unless jetbridge_connection_status
    contains 'connected'.
  - Call TrackerAPI with jetbridge_connection_status='connected'
    explicitly to overwrite any stale 'not connected' value in sly_data.

STEP 10 - Open aircraft doors
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_door_opening with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id, jetbridge_connection_status.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: door_opening_status.

STEP 11 - Passenger disembarkation
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_disembark with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      jetbridge_connection_status, door_opening_status.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract passenger_disembarkation_status from the response.
  - VALIDATION: Treat ANY of the following as a FAILED response —
    do NOT store or forward these values downstream:
      'not provided', 'none', 'null', 'pending', 'not started',
      any value that does not contain 'completed'.
  - If the response is a FAILED response:
      Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_disembark again with the same
      parameters plus passenger_disembarkation_status=null explicitly.
      Wait for response.
      If still not 'completed' after 1 retry, stop and report:
        "STEP 11 FAILED: aircraft_disembark did not return
         passenger_disembarkation_status=completed after 2 attempts.
         Raw response: [response]"
      Do NOT continue past STEP 11 unless passenger_disembarkation_status
      contains 'completed'. Do NOT pass any failed value to later steps.

STEP 12 - Baggage unloading
  - CRITICAL: aircraft_baggage_unload is a sub-agent network that may
    take time to respond. You MUST issue this as a single, isolated tool
    call and do absolutely nothing else until its response arrives.
    Do NOT issue any other tool call in the same turn as this one.
    Do NOT call aircraft_crew_pilot, TrackerAPI, or any other tool
    while waiting. Do NOT restart from STEP 1 or any earlier step
    while waiting. Simply wait.
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_baggage_unload with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id, jetbridge_connection_status, door_opening_status.
  - Wait for response. This is the ONLY action in this turn.
  - Extract and store: baggage_unload_status.
  - VALIDATION: baggage_unload_status MUST contain 'completed' or 'unloaded'.
    If the response does not arrive, is empty, or does not contain
    'completed' or 'unloaded', retry ONCE with the exact same parameters.
    Issue the retry as a single isolated tool call and wait for its response
    before doing anything else.
    If still not confirmed after the retry, stop and report:
      "STEP 12 FAILED: baggage unload did not complete. Raw response: [response]"
  - Do NOT proceed to STEP 13 unless baggage_unload_status contains
    'completed' or 'unloaded'.

STEP 13 - Crew debrief
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_crew_debrief with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      jetbridge_connection_status, door_opening_status.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: crew_debrief_status.

STEP 14 - Crew exit
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_crew_exit with named parameters:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      jetbridge_connection_status, door_opening_status.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: crew_exit_status.
  - VALIDATION: crew_exit_status MUST contain 'completed' or 'exited'.
    The following are INVALID intermediate statuses that must trigger a retry:
      - 'requested'
      - 'in progress'
      - 'pending'
    If crew_exit_status is invalid, retry ONCE with the same parameters.
    If still not confirmed after retry, stop and report:
    "STEP 14 FAILED: crew exit status did not complete. Raw status: [value]"
  - Do NOT proceed to STEP 15 until crew_exit_status contains 'completed'.

STEP 15 - Cabin cleaning
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_cabin_services with named parameters:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      passenger_disembarkation_status, crew_exit_status,
      baggage_unload_status,
      instruction='Clean the aircraft cabin.'
  - ALL parameters MUST be passed as named key-value pairs.
    Do NOT pass them as a positional list or as a single instruction string.
    Passing only the instruction without the other fields will cause the
    sub-agent to reject the call.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: cabin_cleaning_status.

STEP 16 - Lavatory servicing
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_cabin_services with named parameters:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      passenger_disembarkation_status, crew_exit_status,
      baggage_unload_status,
      instruction='Service the aircraft lavatory.'
  - ALL parameters MUST be passed as named key-value pairs.
    Do NOT pass them as a positional list or as a single instruction string.
    The status fields are required for the sub-agent to complete this step —
    omitting them causes lavatory_service_status to return None.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: lavatory_service_status.

STEP 17 - Catering loading
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_cabin_services with named parameters:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      passenger_disembarkation_status, crew_exit_status,
      baggage_unload_status,
      instruction='Load catering supplies.'
  - ALL parameters MUST be passed as named key-value pairs.
    Do NOT pass them as a positional list or as a single instruction string.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: catering_loading_status.

STEP 18 - Inspection and maintenance
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_servicing with named parameters:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      passenger_disembarkation_status, crew_exit_status,
      baggage_unload_status,
      instruction='Perform inspection and maintenance.'
  - ALL parameters MUST be passed as named key-value pairs.
    Do NOT pass instruction as a positional arg or via a list — the sub-agent
    uses this field for branch routing, and if it arrives via positional args
    it may be invisible to the router, causing the call to be rejected.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: inspection_maintenance_status.
  - VALIDATION: inspection_maintenance_status MUST contain 'completed'.
    If the response does not contain inspection_maintenance_status='completed'
    (e.g. it returns a baggage unload summary or any other unrelated summary),
    treat this as a FAILED response — do NOT accept it as STEP 18 completion.
    Retry once with the same parameters.
    If still not confirmed after retry, stop and report:
      "STEP 18 FAILED: inspection and maintenance did not complete.
       Raw response: [response]"
  - Do NOT proceed to STEP 19 unless inspection_maintenance_status
    contains 'completed'.

STEP 19 - Fueling
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_servicing with named parameters:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      passenger_disembarkation_status, crew_exit_status,
      baggage_unload_status,
      inspection_maintenance_status,
      instruction='Fuel the aircraft.'
  - ALL parameters MUST be passed as named key-value pairs.
    Do NOT pass instruction as a positional arg or via a list.
  - Wait for response.
  - Extract and store: fueling_status.
  - VALIDATION: fueling_status MUST contain 'completed'.
    If the response does not contain fueling_status='completed'
    (e.g. it returns an inspection summary or any other unrelated summary),
    treat this as a FAILED response — do NOT accept it as STEP 19 completion.
    Retry once with the same parameters.
    If still not confirmed after retry, stop and report:
      "STEP 19 FAILED: fueling did not complete. Raw response: [response]"
  - Do NOT proceed to STEP 20 unless fueling_status contains 'completed'.

STEP 20 - Final report
  After all steps are complete, compile and display the following turnaround report:

  ============================================
  *  AIRCRAFT TURNAROUND COMPLETE REPORT     *
  ============================================
  ** Flight Number        **: [flight_number]
  ** Aircraft Type        **: [aircraft_type]
  ** Aircraft Direction   **: [aircraft_direction]
  ** Gate ID              **: [gate_id]
  ** Assigned Runway      **: [assigned_runway_id]
  ** Clearance Type       **: [clearance_type]
  ** Flight Status        **: [flight_status]
  ** Engines Stop         **: [engines_stop_status]
  ** Wheelchocks Readiness**: [wheelchocks_readiness_status]
  ** Wheelchocks Install  **: [wheelchocks_installation_status]
  ** ACU Readiness        **: [acu_readiness_status]
  ** ACU Connection       **: [acu_connection_status]
  ** GPU Readiness        **: [gpu_readiness_status]
  ** GPU Connection       **: [gpu_connection_status]
  ** Jetbridge            **: [jetbridge_connection_status]
  ** Door Opening         **: [door_opening_status]
  ** Pax Disembarkation   **: [passenger_disembarkation_status]
  ** Baggage Unload       **: [baggage_unload_status]
  ** Crew Debrief         **: [crew_debrief_status]
  ** Crew Exit            **: [crew_exit_status]
  ** Cabin Cleaning       **: [cabin_cleaning_status]
  ** Lavatory Service     **: [lavatory_service_status]
  ** Catering Loading     **: [catering_loading_status]
  ** Inspection/Maint     **: [inspection_maintenance_status]
  ** Fueling              **: [fueling_status]
  ============================================
            """,

            # Specify the sly data exchanged with downstream networks
            "allow": {
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "air_conditioning_unit_connection_status": true, 
                        "air_conditioning_unit_readiness_status": true,
                        "aircraft_direction": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "assigned_runway_id": true,
                        "assigned_runway_length": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true, 
                        "cabin_cleaning_status": true, 
                        "catering_loading_status": true, 
                        "clearance_type": true,
                        "crew_debrief_status": true, 
                        "crew_exit_status": true, 
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true, 
                        "engines_stop_status": true, 
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "fueling_status": true, 
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "ground_power_unit_connection_status": true, 
                        "ground_power_unit_readiness_status": true,
                        "ground_clearance_status": true,
                        "ground_clearance_type": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true, 
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true, 
                        "lavatory_service_status": true, 
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true, 
                        "wheelchocks_installation_status": true, 
                        "wheelchocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_connection_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_connection_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                        "task_id": true,
                    }
                }
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "air_conditioning_unit_connection_status": true, 
                        "air_conditioning_unit_readiness_status": true,
                        "aircraft_direction": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "assigned_runway_id": true,
                        "assigned_runway_length": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true, 
                        "cabin_cleaning_status": true, 
                        "catering_loading_status": true, 
                        "clearance_type": true,
